The second, the recovery of the Mark, even though now it seems to be science fiction, with a very favorable opinion stream, almost 50% of the population.
Thirdly, a new Euro concept, in line with the German proposals for greater macroeconomic control, budgetary rigor, fines to the countries that violate them, possible suspensions of payments to one of them and extension to the private sector of the costs of potential adjustments.
The German position is clear and it has long been defining itself, so now there is no room for excuses.
First, in 2009, when both the IMF and the European Commission were stimulating the deficits, the German government invented a constitutional reform to prevent them from 2016.
