Secondly, the idea that any hacker can capture the most secret secrets of the world’s most powerful country brings a non-negotiable blow to the prestige of the State Department.
So the scandal does not put victims in crisis as well as the "burrests".
But let’s get to the deep nature of what happened.
Once upon a time, in Orwell’s time, every power could be conceived as a Big Brother who controlled every gesture of its subjects.
The Orwellian prophecy had been fully proven since, being able to control every movement through the telephone, every transaction made, the hotel visited, the motorway borrowed, and so on, the citizen became the total victim of the eye of power.
But when it is shown, as it is now, that even the crypts of the secrets of power cannot escape the control of a hacker, the control report ceases to be unidirectional and becomes circular.
